  "description": "This dish was inspired by our winter trip to Valencia, Spain. One day we had an amazing lunch with lobster in brothy rice. We like it much more than paella, and we wanted to have a similar recipe that we could cook at home (minus the lobster). This is arroz caldoso _de pollo_ (soupy rice _with chicken_), and it's made of a few simple ingredients, a bunch of spices, and cooks in one pot. Still, it has enough flavor and warmth to make a whole family happy.",
